, England"},"en":{"1184–":"1184–Deceased","1180–Male":"1180–Deceased","1198–1272":"1198–1272","1184–Female":"1184–Deceased","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1184":"1184","1272":"1272","1180":"1180","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"England","Pyvelesdon, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lewis","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English, Old French personal name <i>Lewis</i>, <i>Leweis</i>, <i>Lowis</i>, from ancient Germanic (originally West Frankish) <i>Hludwig</i> (itself from <i>hlōd-</i> ‘fame, famous’ + <i>wīg-</i> ‘battle’). This was Latinized as <i>Ludovicus</i> and <i>Chlodovisus</i>, which were gallicized as <i>Clovis</i> or <i>Clouis</i>, French <i>Louis</i>. The name may also appear as <i>Lawis</i>, <i>Laweys</i>, <i>Lawes</i>, by unrounding of the vowel of <i>Lowis</i> on the analogy of the variation between <i>Low</i> and <i>Law</i> as pet forms of Middle English <i>Lourence</i> alias <i>Laurence</i>. This surname is also very common among African Americans. See   Laws   2 and compare   Lawrence  .","Welsh: adopted for the Welsh personal name <i>Llywelyn</i> (see   Llewellyn  ).","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Lughaidh</b> ‘son of <i>Lughaidh</i>’. This is one of the most common Old Irish personal names. It is derived from <i>Lugh</i> ‘brightness’, which was the name of a Celtic god."],"variants":[{"name":"Laws","meanings":["English: variant of   Law   (pet form of   Lawrence  ), with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Perhaps a shortened form of Scottish or Irish   McLeish  . Compare   McLaws  ."]},{"name":"Lewison","meanings":["Welsh and English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name   Lewis   (in Wales this was taken as equivalent to the Welsh personal name   Llewelyn  ). In North America, this surname has reportedly absorbed in some cases the Greek patronymic   Iliopoulos  .","Jewish (Ashkenazic): patronymic from the personal name <i>Lewi</i>, Polish-influenced form of   Levy  ."]},{"name":"McGlew","meanings":["Irish: most probably from <b>Mac Lughaidh</b> ‘son of <i>Lughaidh</i>’, a Gaelic personal name (referencing the god Lugh), sometimes Anglicized as   Lewis  . However, both Woulfe and MacLysaght consider <i>McGlew</i> to be a shortened form of <b>Mac Dhuinnshléibhe</b> (see   McAleavey   and   Dunleavy  )."]},{"name":"Lowis","meanings":["English: variant of   Lewis   1."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":31,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":40,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":75,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Lewis was born in 1184, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England. She had at least 1 son with Sir Richard de Puleston. She died in England."},"et":{"1184–":"1184–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1198–1272":"1198–1272","1184–Female":"1184–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1184":"1184","1272":"1272","1180":"1180","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"England","Pyvelesdon, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1184–":"1184–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1198–1272":"1198–1272","1184–Female":"1184–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1184":"1184","1272":"1272","1180":"1180","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","England":"England","Pyvelesdon, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"1184–":"1184–Décédée","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1198–1272":"1198–1272","1184–Female":"1184–Décédée","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1198":"1198","1184":"1184","1272":"1272","1180":"1180","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Pyvelesdon, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice Lewis est née en 1184, à Oxford, Oxfordshire, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Richard de Puleston. Elle est décédée à Angleterre."},"de":{